  "summary": "sensivity ships obfuscated payload and PowerShell-spawning launcher",
  "details": "The package contains launcher.js which imports child_process and executes multiple PowerShell commands via execSync (lines 166, 177, 186, 281), alongside HTTP GET activity. It also ships server.obf.js, a heavily obfuscated single-line bundle using hex-mangled identifiers (_0x1ac675, _0x2cdfd8, etc.) — a shape consistent with deliberately concealed payload code. The combination of a PowerShell-spawning launcher, outbound HTTP, and an obfuscated server module in a package whose name is a typo of 'sensitivity' is characteristic of a Windows-targeted dropper / RAT. Installing or running this package on a Windows host will execute arbitrary attacker-defined PowerShell.",
